39064|"the science of thought-form, it is supposed to imply a world of fixed or"|FALSE
39064|"stereotyped relations between ideas, a system of stable thoughts governed"|FALSE
39064|"by inflexible laws in an absolute order of immemorial or eternal truth. As"|FALSE
39064|"against such fixity, psychology is supposed to deal with these same ideas"|FALSE
39064|"as products—as growing out of a living process of thought—having a history"|FALSE
39064|"behind them and perhaps a prospect of further change. The genesis so given"|FALSE
39064|"may be either a mere chronicle-history, or it may be a philosophical"|FALSE
