39064|"of means and ends and presuppose a normative or critical function which"|FALSE
39064|"has classified reality. Psychically, the elements which enter into"|FALSE
39064|"knowledge are not other than those which belong to opinion: but they are"|FALSE
39064|"nearer an adequate rendering of reality, they are truer, or nearer the"|FALSE
39064|"Idea. And in the main we may say, that is truer or more real which"|FALSE
39064|"succeeds in more completely organising and unifying elements—which rises"|FALSE
39064|"more and more above the selfish or isolated part into the thorough unity"|FALSE
39064|"of all parts."|FALSE
39064|"The superior faculty is therefore the more thorough organisation of that"|FALSE
39064|"which is elsewhere less harmoniously systematised. Opinion is fragmentary"|FALSE
39064|"and partial: it begins abruptly and casually from the unknown, and runs"|FALSE
