39064|"morally important. It is a faculty, because it means that actually its"|FALSE
39064|"possessor has ordered and systematised his life or his ideas of things."|FALSE
39064|"Psychologically, it, like unreason, is a compound of elements: but in the"|FALSE
39064|"case of reason the composition is unendingly and infinitely consistent; it"|FALSE
39064|"is knowledge completely unified. The distinction then is not in the"|FALSE
39064|"strictest sense psychological: for it has an aesthetic or normative"|FALSE
