39064|"eternal self. So, in Plato, the man of heart is but a nature which by fits"|FALSE
39064|"and starts, or with steady but limited vision, realises the larger life."|FALSE
39064|"These parts or kinds are not separate and co-existent faculties: but"|FALSE
39064|"grades in the co-ordination and unification of the same one human nature."|FALSE
39064|"(i.) Psychology and Epistemology."|FALSE
39064|"Psychology however in the strict sense is extremely difficult to define."|FALSE
39064|"Those who describe it as the “science of mind,” the “phenomenology of"|FALSE
39064|"consciousness,” seem to give it a wider scope than they really mean. The"|FALSE
