39064|"certainty which claims to be necessary and universal, which pledges its"|FALSE
39064|"whole self for its assertion. Fichte thus unifies and accentuates the"|FALSE
39064|"common element in the Kantian criticisms. In the first of these Kant had"|FALSE
39064|"begun by explaining the nature and limitation of empirical science. It was"|FALSE
