39064|"The first stage in mental development is the establishment of regular and"|FALSE
39064|"uniform relations between soul and body: it is the differentiation of"|FALSE
39064|"organs and the integration of function: the balance between sensation and"|FALSE
39064|"movement, between the afferent and efferent processes of sensitivity."|FALSE
39064|"Given a potential soul, the problem is to make it actual in an individual"|FALSE
39064|"body. It is the business of a physical psychology to describe in detail"|FALSE
39064|"the steps by which the body we are attached to is made inward as our idea"|FALSE
39064|"through the several organs and their nervous appurtenances: whereas a"|FALSE
39064|"psychical physiology would conversely explain the corresponding processes"|FALSE
