39064|"natural world of ethics—where true moral life has not yet arisen—this is"|FALSE
39064|"mere retaliation or the _lex talionis_;—the beginning of an endless series"|FALSE
39064|"of vengeance and counter-vengeance, the blood-feud. Punishment, in the"|FALSE
39064|"stricter sense of the term,—which looks both to antecedents and effects in"|FALSE
39064|"character—cannot yet come into existence; for to punish there must be"|FALSE
39064|"something superior to individualities, an ethical idea embodied in an"|FALSE
39064|"institution, to which the injurer and the injured alike belong. But as yet"|FALSE
39064|"punishment is only vengeance, the personal and natural equivalent, the"|FALSE
39064|"physical reaction against injury, perhaps regulated and formulated by"|FALSE
