39064|"perhaps grudgingly rendered."|FALSE
39064|"Of the peasant order Hegel has less to say. On one side the “country” as"|FALSE
39064|"opposed to the “town” has a closer natural sympathy with the common and"|FALSE
39064|"general interest: and the peasantry is the undifferentiated, solid and"|FALSE
