39064|"object."|FALSE
39064|"§ 425. Abstract self-consciousness is the first negation of consciousness,"|FALSE
39064|"and for that reason it is burdened with an external object, or, nominally,"|FALSE
39064|"with the negation of it. Thus it is at the same time the antecedent stage,"|FALSE
