39064|"produced by the mind when developing itself as _objective_ mind—a"|FALSE
39064|"development in which the _content_ of autonomous action loses its"|FALSE
39064|"contingency and optionality. The discussion of the true intrinsic worth of"|FALSE
39064|"the impulses, inclinations, and passions is thus essentially the theory of"|FALSE
39064|"legal, moral, and social _duties_."|FALSE
39064|"§ 475. The subject is the act of satisfying impulses, an act of (at least)"|FALSE
39064|"formal rationality, as it translates them from the subjectivity of content"|FALSE
39064|"(which so far is _purpose_) into objectivity, where the subject is made to"|FALSE
39064|"close with itself. If the content of the impulse is distinguished as the"|FALSE
39064|"thing or business from this act of carrying it out, and we regard the"|FALSE
39064|"thing which has been brought to pass as containing the element of"|FALSE
