39064|"§ 476. The will, as thinking and implicitly free, distinguishes itself"|FALSE
39064|"from the particularity of the impulses, and places itself as simple"|FALSE
39064|"subjectivity of thought above their diversified content. It is thus"|FALSE
39064|"“reflecting” will."|FALSE
39064|"§ 477. Such a particularity of impulse has thus ceased to be a mere datum:"|FALSE
39064|"the reflective will now sees it as its own, because it closes with it and"|FALSE
